.TH ORCHESTRATE-PARALLEL-AUTONOMOUS-RUNS 1 "2026-07-18" "v0.1.0"
.SH NAME
orchestrate-parallel-autonomous-runs \- validate and coordinate isolated autonomous Spec Kit campaigns
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B orchestrate-parallel-autonomous-runs.sh
-Action ACTION -Manifest PATH -RunnerConfig PATH [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Validates campaign identity, repositories, worker DAG, runner profiles, and
consolidation policy. Start creates one branch and linked worktree per worker,
executes no more than three runner processes, and stores resumable aggregate
state. Stop is cooperative and does not kill processes.
.SH ACTIONS
Validate, Start, Status, Stop, Resume, and Consolidate.
.SH SAFETY
Runner arguments are passed as an executable argument array without shell
evaluation. Installation grants no autonomous execution or remote authority.
Alternative solutions require human selection. Merge-and-sync requires an
all-ready barrier.
.SH SEE ALSO
speckit.parallel-autonomous, speckit.autonomous
